Gauteng province is the new epicentre of COVID-19 infections in the country with over 100, 000 confirmed cases. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize has welcomed a new batch of nurses deployed to hospitals around Gauteng. The deployment of the nurses is part of efforts to bulk up the response to the coronavirus. Despite the rapid increase in the number of coronavirus cases in Gauteng, Mkhize says steps are in place to ensure that medical facilities act quickly. The province's numbers are expected to soar in the coming weeks. WATCH: Mkhize says alcohol ban evidence-based Gauteng has become the coronavirus epicentre with the province recording 103,713 infections and 644 deaths. Mkhize said the rapid daily increase in cases is concerning. "The sudden increase is what really shocked the system," Mkhize said. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Health minister Zweli Mkhize and Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku are at the George Mukhari hospital. Courtesy #DStv403